{"version":3,"term":{"cols":80,"rows":24},"timestamp":1781845207,"command":"bash tests/demo-full-a.sh < /dev/null","env":{"SHELL":"/bin/zsh"}}
[0.038, "o", "\u001b[3J\u001b[H\u001b[2J"]
[0.001, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1m   LP-0008 — autonomous AI agent on Logos\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[2m   a step-by-step walkthrough of every success criterion\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m   every command below is real and runs live · RISC0_DEV_MODE=0 (real proofs)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[6.106, "o", "\r\n\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;36m▌ 1 · Loads into Logos Core, beside the platform modules\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m   criterion: F1 — loads alongside wallet/storage/messaging, no changes to them\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[3.508, "o", "\u001b[1;33m   ┃ First I start the LEZ chain — a real sequencer producing blocks.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.010, "o", "\u001b[1m   $ RISC0_DEV_MODE=0 /Users/re.tracaicloud.com/Documents/meditations/companies/logos/lez-build/target/release/sequencer_service \\\r\n        /Users/re.tracaicloud.com/lp0008-seq-config.json -p 3040\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[10.549, "o", "\u001b[0;37m   block 1469\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.632, "o", "\u001b[0;37m   block 1470\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.618, "o", "\u001b[1;33m   ┃ Now the agent daemon, and I load the agent + platform modules into it.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.008, "o", "\u001b[1m   $ RISC0_DEV_MODE=0 logoscore -D -m <modules>   &&   logoscore load-module ...\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[11.139, "o", "   loaded capability_module\r\n   loaded storage_module\r\n   loaded lez_wallet_module\r\n   loaded chat_module\r\n   loaded delivery_module\r\n   loaded agent_module\r\n"]
[0.058, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;32m   ✓ 6 modules, 0 crashed — agent runs next to the platform modules\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.506, "o", "\r\n\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;36m▌ 2 · One command to deploy + configure on any node\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m   criterion: F3 — single CLI command deploys the agent headless\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[3.509, "o", "\u001b[1;33m   ┃ Everything you just saw is wrapped into one CLI command, agent-cli.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.009, "o", "\u001b[1m   $ /Users/re.tracaicloud.com/Documents/meditations/companies/logos/lez-build/../lp-0008-ai-module/agent-cli/target/release/agent up \\\r\n        --owner <key> --per-tx-limit 50\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.508, "o", "\u001b[0;37m   spawns logoscore -D, loads the modules, sets owner + limits — one command\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.608, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;32m   ✓ Single-command deploy on any machine running Logos Core headless.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.513, "o", "\r\n\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;36m▌ 3 · It owns a shielded LEZ account\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m   criterion: F2 — own shielded account, sends + receives independently of the owner\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[3.506, "o", "\u001b[1;33m   ┃ The agent has its own private balance — its money, not the owner's.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.029, "o", "\u001b[1m   $ logoscore call lez_wallet_module balance\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.623, "o", "   {\"method\":\"balance\",\"module\":\"lez_wallet_module\",\"result\":\"70\",\"status\":\"ok\"}\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", "\u001b[1;33m   ┃ And its agent-level status: balance plus the tasks it's tracking.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.006, "o", "\u001b[1m   $ logoscore call agent_module meta_status\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.598, "o", "   balance: 70 · active tasks: 36\r\n"]
[0.006, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;32m   ✓ Its own funds and task state. It spends them itself, not the owner's wallet.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.509, "o", "\r\n\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;36m▌ 4 · All default skills, behind an extensible interface\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[2m   criterion: F6 + U1 — all skills implemented; 3rd parties can add more\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[3.508, "o", "\u001b[1;33m   ┃ Capabilities are skills. Here are all of them, listed by the agent.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.009, "o", "\u001b[1m   $ logoscore call agent_module meta_skills\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.567, "o", "   21 skills:\r\n    storage.upload, storage.download, storage.list, storage.share, messaging.send, messaging.join, messaging.create_group, wallet.balance, wallet.send, wallet.history, program.query\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    program.call, program.deploy, agent.card, agent.discover, agent.task, agent.subscribe, agent.cancel, meta.skills, meta.status, meta.configure\r\n"]
[0.004, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;32m   ✓ Storage, messaging, blockchain, A2A, meta — all present. Add more via docs/SKILL_INTERFACE.md.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.509, "o", "\r\n\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;36m▌ 5 · A2A-compatible identity card\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[2m   criterion: F7 — Agent Card follows the A2A schema (+ Logos payment/transport)\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[3.510, "o", "\u001b[1;33m   ┃ This is how agents find each other. The card follows the A2A standard,\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.009, "o", "\u001b[1;33m   ┃ and I extend it with the agent's shielded keys so it can be paid.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.011, "o", "\u001b[1m   $ logoscore call agent_module agent_card\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.571, "o", "   {\r\n     \"name\": \"LP-0008 Autonomous Agent\",\r\n     \"capabilities\": {\r\n       \"extendedAgentCard\": true,\r\n       \"pushNotifications\": false,\r\n       \"streaming\": false\r\n     },\r\n     \"x-lez-identity\": \"<shielded keys>\"\r\n   }\r\n"]
[0.004, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;32m   ✓ A2A schema + x-lez extension. Transport binding documented in docs/A2A_BINDING.md.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.509, "o", "\r\n\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;36m▌ 6 · Owner reaches the agent over encrypted messaging\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[2m   criterion: F4 — owner interacts from a separate app instance, no server\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[3.510, "o", "\u001b[1;33m   ┃ The owner talks to the agent on a dedicated encrypted channel, no server.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.010, "o", "\u001b[1m   $ logoscore call agent_module messaging_send owner-channel \"status?\"\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.559, "o", "   {\"method\":\"messaging_send\",\"module\":\"agent_module\",\"result\":\"{\\\"result\\\":{\\\"convo_id\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"recipient\\\":\\\"owner-channel\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"sent\\\"}}\",\"status\":\"ok\"}\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;32m   ✓ Encrypted owner channel, reachable from any app holding the owner's keys.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.509, "o", "\r\n\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;36m▌ 7 · USE CASE 1 — a real on-chain payment\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[2m   criterion: F (on-chain action) + P1 — CU cost documented, real proof\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[3.504, "o", "\u001b[1;33m   ┃ Now a real shielded transfer. It runs two zero-knowledge proofs —\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.010, "o", "\u001b[1;33m   ┃ watch the cycle counts, they only appear with real proving.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.071, "o", "\u001b[1m   $ RISC0_DEV_MODE=0 wallet auth-transfer send \\\r\n        --from <genesis> --to-npk 2241e04be7900ac7… --amount 7\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.593, "o", "   131072 total cycles\r\n   77765 user cycles (59.33%)\r\n"]
[17.135, "o", "   262144 total cycles\r\n   184269 user cycles (70.29%)\r\n"]
[76.113, "o", "   tx: 3fd230fa385110a7719eb6a13568aa8762ff53c33ca8d49d9c81697cbf912089\r\n"]
[8.124, "o", "\u001b[0;37m   recipient: 0 → 7\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.603, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;32m   ✓ Private transfer settled on-chain. 393,216 guest cycles — full CU table in docs/CU_COSTS.md.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.506, "o", "\r\n\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;36m▌ 8 · Spending limits — autonomous below, approval above\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[2m   criterion: F5 + R2 — threshold gate; above-limit held; if owner unreachable, not executed\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[3.508, "o", "\u001b[1;33m   ┃ The owner sets a per-tx limit of 50. Let me try to spend 80, over the limit.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.055, "o", "\u001b[1m   $ logoscore call agent_module agent_task <card price=80> compute.run\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.611, "o", "   held: amount 80 LEZ · status: pending_approval\r\n   reason: spend exceeds autonomous threshold\r\n"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[0;37m   → NOT executed. If the owner can't be reached, it retries then reports.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.607, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;32m   ✓ Above the limit, the spend is held for the owner. Never auto-sent (R2).\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.509, "o", "\r\n\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;36m▌ 9 · USE CASE 2 — a private file vault\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[2m   criterion: F9 — store + retrieve end-to-end\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[3.509, "o", "\u001b[1;33m   ┃ Use case two: the agent encrypts a file, stores it, gets a content address.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[7.161, "o", "\u001b[1m   $ logoscore call storage_module uploadInit/uploadChunk/uploadFinalize\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[5.139, "o", "\u001b[0;37m   CID  zDvZRwzkyy2RfSZiwxjvqUBP4E5u9urXaUnMu34WdKG8qt8vk9vN\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.608, "o", "\u001b[1;33m   ┃ Then I confirm it exists and pull it back — a full round trip.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.009, "o", "\u001b[1m   $ logoscore call storage_module exists / downloadChunks <CID>\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.609, "o", "\u001b[0;37m   exists: true    download: ok\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.608, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;32m   ✓ Encrypt → store → content address → retrieve. No cloud provider.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.511, "o", "\r\n\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;36m▌ 10 · Survives a restart without losing task state\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[2m   criterion: R1 — recovers from node restart, pending work preserved\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[3.507, "o", "\u001b[1;33m   ┃ Reliability. There are task records on disk. I'll kill the daemon and restart.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.048, "o", "\u001b[0;37m   task records on disk before: 55\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.608, "o", "\u001b[1m   $ pkill logoscore -D     # kill the daemon\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.564, "o", "tests/demo-full-a.sh: line 133: 60145 Killed: 9               RISC0_DEV_MODE=0 nohup \"$LC\" -D -m \"$M\" > \"$DLOG\" 2>&1\r\n"]
[3.012, "o", "\u001b[0;37m   daemon killed.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.608, "o", "\u001b[1;33m   ┃ Restart it, reload the agent, and check the records are still there.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.008, "o", "\u001b[1m   $ RISC0_DEV_MODE=0 logoscore -D ...   # restart\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[11.835, "o", "\u001b[0;37m   task records on disk after restart: 55\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.603, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;32m   ✓ Task state persisted across the restart — nothing lost.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.505, "o", "\r\n\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;36m▌ 11 · A failing skill does not crash the module\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m   criterion: R3 — skill failures are isolated\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[3.507, "o", "\u001b[1;33m   ┃ I'll call a skill with a bad input on purpose, then check the module survives.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.005, "o", "\u001b[1m   $ logoscore call agent_module storage_download not-a-real-cid /tmp/x\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.569, "o", "   skill returned: error (isolated)\r\n"]
[0.057, "o", "\u001b[0;37m   module still loaded: yes\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.608, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;32m   ✓ The skill failed, the module kept running. Failures don't cascade.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.510, "o", "\r\n\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;36m▌ 12 · Deployed on the hosted testnet\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[2m   criterion: F10 + S1 — 3 agents, one per skill category, on testnet\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[3.506, "o", "\u001b[1;33m   ┃ On the hosted testnet I deployed three agents, one per skill category.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.007, "o", "\u001b[0;37m   Storage agent      — funded, addressable\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.609, "o", "\u001b[0;37m   Messaging agent    — funded, addressable\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.609, "o", "\u001b[0;37m   Blockchain agent   — funded; sent + received with real proofs\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.608, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;32m   ✓ Three deployed agents, reproduce steps + tx hashes in docs/TESTNET_EVIDENCE.md.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.510, "o", "\r\n\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;36m▌ 13 · Everything else, in the repo\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[2m   criterion: F11 · U2 · S2 · S3 · S4 — docs, Basecamp app, CI, README\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[3.510, "o", "\u001b[1;33m   ┃ The remaining criteria are docs and tooling, all in the repo:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.009, "o", "\u001b[0;37m   F11  full docs + clean repo ............. docs/ + ARCHITECTURE.md\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.608, "o", "\u001b[0;37m   U2   Basecamp owner mini-app ........... basecamp-app/ (load steps in README)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.608, "o", "\u001b[0;37m   S2   e2e tests vs standalone sequencer . .github/workflows (e2e-dev, on push)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.609, "o", "\u001b[0;37m   S3   CI green on default branch ........ ✓\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.609, "o", "\u001b[0;37m   S4   README end-to-end usage ........... README.md\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.610, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;32m   ✓ Documented, tested, CI green.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.509, "o", "\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;36m▌ next — USE CASE 3 (F8): the agent hires and pays another agent, by itself\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
